# Audit: Reschedule & Cancel

## 11. Reschedule & Cancel
- [x] Verify Moving a Booking (update date/time/staff/services)
- [x] Verify Cancelling a Booking (status update, notifications)
- [x] Verify Availability is updated correctly when a booking is moved or cancelled
- [x] Verify Conflict Prevention works when rescheduling (prevent double booking)

## 12. Salon Public Page
- [x] Step 1: Fetch Salon Public Info (status='active', is_active=1, etc.)
- [x] Step 2: Fetch Public Services (grouped by category)
- [x] Step 3: Fetch Public Staff (who can perform services)
- [x] Step 4: Fetch Staff per Service Mapping (Active/Visible only)
- [x] Step 5: Fetch Public Photos (gallery or salon_photos, sorted by display_order, include cover)
- [x] Step 6: Fetch Public Reviews (approved only, avg rating, total count)
- [x] Step 7: Booking Widget Link (dynamic salon_id, no hardcoding, widget APIs verified)
- [x] Step 8: Performance (inlined business_hours query, parallel fetches, Cache-Control headers)
- [x] Step 9: Security (no internal_notes, no SELECT *, pricing gate, all filters server-side)
- [x] Step 10: Documentation completed

## 13. Salon Search Page
- [x] Step 1: Basic Salon Search (name, city, category, is_marketplace_enabled, pagination, N+1 fixed)
- [x] Step 2: Filters (city exact match, category, price_level<=, all server-side)
- [x] Step 3: Salon Profile Link (dynamic /salon/[id], 404 on disabled salons, verified)
